title: Bali Handara Gate
address: Jl. Raya Singaraja-Denpasar, Pancasari, Kec. Sukasada, Kabupaten Buleleng, Bali 81161
note_from_owner:
Bali Handara Gate is located in Pancasari Village Bedugul, the central highlands of Bali and nestled down inside the crater of an extinct volcano at an altitude of almost 1,400 meters (almost 4,000 feet) above sea level.

This is one of the most Instagrammed spot on the island. It's become a must-visit place among tourists and photography lover.

Handara Gate is actually the entrance to a golf resort. The traditional Hindu gate symbolises the entrance from the outer world to the temple, or in this case, golf course, and plays an important role in Indonesian culture, particularly in Bali.

address: Gg. Beji No.35, Ubud, Kecamatan Ubud, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80571
note_from_owner:
Puri Kauhan Ubud is one of Balinese cultural heritage which is located in the cultural heart of the Island of the Gods in Ubud, Gianyar.

Established since the 19th century, Puri Kauhan Ubud has become part of the history of Bali and Indonesia. Puri Kauhan Ubud keeps historical records, cultural stories, and Balinese literature in manuscripts made from coconut tree leaves – also known as Lontar.

We invite all parties to explore the history and culture of Bali and Indonesia at Puri Kauhan Ubud.
